{"entity_timestamp": "2026-03-29T06:25:18+00:00", "entity_id": "69ff16e1-9492-5ab2-bea5-8bff628b84c6", "alert": {"header_text": "Planned work: Albion Station car park", "description_text": "Monday 2 February to late 2026 A new Albion Station will be built as part of Stage 1 of Melbourne Airport Rail and the Sunshine Superhub project. In order to complete major underground service relocation works, Albion Station car park will be closed. Alternative parking will be available at Tottenham Station on Rupert Street. Albion Station, access to platforms and drop off and pick up zones remain open during this time. Accessible car spaces Eight accessible car spaces at Albion Station will remain open. Shared use path closure A section of the shared use path will be closed at the southern end of the car park. Pedestrian and cyclist detours will be in place during this time.", "severity_level": null, "cause": "OTHER_CAUSE", "effect": "OTHER_EFFECT", "informed_entities": [{"agency_id": "1", "route_id": "aus:vic:vic-02-SUY:", "direction_id": 0, "stop_id": "vic:rail:ALB"}, {"agency_id": "1", "route_id": "aus:vic:vic-02-SUY:", "direction_id": 1, "stop_id": "vic:rail:ALB"}], "active_periods": [{"start": "2026-01-31T20:00:00+00:00", "end": "2026-12-31T07:00:00+00:00"}]}, "ingest_timestamp": "2026-03-29T06:25:56+00:00"}
{"entity_timestamp": "2026-03-29T06:25:18+00:00", "entity_id": "10955b17-724e-5d66-b5f6-0c116e59f89a", "alert": {"header_text": "Planned work: Watsonia Station car park changes", "description_text": "From April 2024 to 2028 The Watsonia Station car park has been closed since April 2024. From October 2025, there will be changes for pedestrians, cars, and buses accessing Watsonia Station as part of ongoing works for M80 Ring Road Completion.  new DDA-compliant paths and upgraded crossings to improve safety and accessibility for pedestrians. one-way entrance from Greensborough Highway northbound and a new signalised intersection for exiting vehicles. relocated bus stop and streamlined loop to support service reliability and reduce congestion.  These changes will be in place until a new Watsonia Station car park is built later in the project. We’re planning our work in the station precinct to minimise disruptions.  no changes to the pedestrian overpass or station platform access. maintaining accessible parking and drop-off and pick-up areas near the station entrance. providing more than 500 parking spaces at the nearby Watsonia Station commuter car park.", "severity_level": null, "cause": "OTHER_CAUSE", "effect": "OTHER_EFFECT", "informed_entities": [{"agency_id": "1", "route_id": "aus:vic:vic-02-HBE:", "direction_id": 1, "stop_id": "vic:rail:WAT"}, {"agency_id": "1", "route_id": "aus:vic:vic-02-HBE:", "direction_id": 0, "stop_id": "vic:rail:WAT"}, {"agency_id": "1", "route_id": "aus:vic:vic-02-HBE-R:", "direction_id": 0, "stop_id": "vic:rail:WAT"}, {"agency_id": "1", "route_id": "aus:vic:vic-02-HBE-R:", "direction_id": 1, "stop_id": "vic:rail:WAT"}], "active_periods": [{"start": "2024-04-03T19:00:00+00:00", "end": "2028-01-01T07:00:00+00:00"}]}, "ingest_timestamp": "2026-03-29T06:25:56+00:00"}
